THE second Beer Buffet Festival will take place in Soweto next month. The event, hosted by DJ and producer Vonani “King Vee” Mashila will bring alcohol, food and music to the Soweto Cricket Oval Stadium in Moroka on 26 March. King Vee told SunBuzz: “The festival was previously known as Soweto Beer Buffet Festival, but we changed the name. “However, like the first one, it’s for the people by the people, bringing you the latest beers, ciders, spirits and wine. He said the event will give up-and-coming musicians a chance to perform. ALSO READ : TEARY LACONCO SHARES ABOUT ZUMA SPLIT! “In the previous festival, we created a great buzz and interest. It focused on artists who have already made it big. “This year, we will focus more on up-and-coming artists and uplift them. “It will be the same with the alcohol brands. We’re going with new brands of alcohol in and around Soweto. “We’ll release the formal line-up next month.” “I see the festival as a tasting event for every alcohol brand available in South Africa, and an opportunity for those brands to gain a market in Soweto and to grow their income.” The DJ said people should prepare themselves for a fun day and be open to new experiences. “People can look forward to an entertaining night, and a wide range of the best-tasting beers, ciders, spirits and wine. “We want people to always know they have plenty to choose from. “It’s important for everyone coming to experience everything,” he said. General tickets cost R350 and VIP R650 on the Location Ticket website.